snippet.textDisplay:
never before in the history of professinal boxing have i seen such disgraceful and unsportsmanship behaviour. it is a massive disappointment that a boxing match of this magnitude has been overshadowed by the childish and disrespectful antics of two combatants at the top of their game.
people that attract massive attention should bear in mind that their behaviour might be emulated by impressionable members of the sport and members of the general public. seeing this behaviour might be considered normal and acceptable. even desirable. both men are fathers and husbands, is this how they want their children and family to see them. even though big john fury is tyson`s biggest fan he can`t be happy with this and he wont be alone. dignity in all things is important and is a measure of a mans integrity without it he has nothing and can never become a true champion. rise to the top in all things and be proud of your achievements but give respect and try and conduct yourself in the manner of a decent man, achieving that and that alone is a greater achievement than winning a boxing match.
